parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine oil consumption can lead to engine failure, causing the vehicle to stall or leave the driver stranded, which can lead to accidents or other safety risks.
symptoms: Burning a quart or more of oil per week
frequent oil changes
no visible oil leaks
knocking or unusual engine noises
engine failure
sudden loss of oil pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected shattering of the sunroof can cause a loud noise, which can startle the driver and lead to loss of control, accidents, or injuries from flying glass.
symptoms: The sunroof shatters suddenly and without warning
often with a loud noise
and can occur even when the vehicle is stationary or moving at a slow speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning sun visor can obstruct the driver's view, leading to reduced visibility, accidents, or injuries, especially during critical driving maneuvers or in bad weather conditions.
symptoms: The sun visor fails to stay in position
falls
or remains in the lowest possible position
obstructing the driver's view and making it difficult to drive safely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause a delay in response from the vehicle when braking, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floorboard when depressed
there is a delay in response from the vehicle when braking
the brake pedal has zero resistance
the vehicle fails to slow down when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dislodging of the fuel filler tank cap can cause fuel spills, which can lead to fires or other accidents.
symptoms: The fuel filler tank cap dislodges when refueling
fuel spills from the tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The catastrophic failure of the tire sidewall can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The tire suddenly loses air
the tire blows out while driving
the tire tread becomes detached from the interior side wall
the tire sidewall cracks
the tire requires frequent air pressure checks and additions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The continuous loss of air pressure in the tire can lead to reduced traction, increased stopping distance, and increased risk of tire failure, which can cause accidents and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The tire pressure monitoring system (TPMS) warning light illuminates
the tire requires frequent air pressure checks and additions
the tire feels soft or spongy
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving.
